author: Ricky O'Donnell
title: Kansas’ Josh Jackson has perfected Kevin Love-like full court outlet passes
text:
Touchdown, Jayhawks.
Start Josh Jackson at quarterback. Maybe try him out in centerfield. Kansas’ superstar freshman has made a habit out of these one-handed, full-court outlet passes, and he did it again against West Virginia on Monday.
Jackson had a similar pass in Kansas’ last game against Texas Tech on Saturday.
Touchdown, Kansas. Josh Jackson with the outlet pic.twitter.com/582eKVdemu 
— Ricky O'Donnell (@SBN_Ricky) February 11, 2017 We told you Jackson is an amazing passer , but this is just next level.
